# Since there's no input source / layout switching support,
# hack-in a parallel tracking of the current input source.
:: cyrillic
alt - space ; cyrillic : input-method-select com.apple.keylayout.RussianWin
cyrillic < alt - space ; default : input-method-select com.apple.keylayout.ABC

# Swap : and ;
0x29 | shift - 0x29
shift - 0x29 | 0x29

# Map the useless § and ± keys to useful ` ~ ones
# Also to match the physical US layout
0x0a | 0x32
shift - 0x0a | shift - 0x32

# It is possible to treat the Fn button both as a modifier and
# as a single-tap with different codes. You just need to map Caps to Fn in
# MacOS "Customize modifier keys" settings.
# See https://github.com/koekeishiya/skhd/issues/1#issuecomment-2538579486
#   0xb3 | escape
#   fn - c | ctrl - c
# However, I find it more useful to just map Caps to Ctrl.
# For Vim, I got used to kj for Esc.
